"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140873","Department for International Development","false","2019-08-05","<p>The UK tracks Yemen’s imports and ports to monitor trends and predict pressure points in humanitarian supplies. We work with the private sector, non-governmental organisations and United Nations agencies to improve our understanding of how Aden Port functions and to advise the United Arab Emirates who are leading international efforts to improve Aden Port.</p><p> </p><p>The UK regularly raises humanitarian concerns with both parties to the conflict, calling on them to comply with UN Security Council Resolution 2451 and facilitate safe, rapid, and unhindered access for humanitarian and commercial supplies, including through Aden Port.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson",,"2019-08-05T16:22:44.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140873/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140873/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-07-22","Yemen: International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the processing time for humanitarian supplies imported through the port of Aden in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","280387"
