"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140964","Cabinet Office","false","2019-07-25","<p>The Government maintains an estimate of the annual cost of electoral registration. This is supported by cost data from Electoral Registration Officers and volume data provided by electoral management systems and other sources of information.</p><p>The Government recognises that Electoral Registration Officers within local authorities are best placed to make decisions on how best to target their work to ensure their electoral registers are complete and accurate. We welcome the sharing of best practice between local authorities on increasing levels of registration. The Electoral Commission provides guidance for EROs and sets and monitors their performance against standards under their Performance Standards Framework, details of which can be found on the EC’s website https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-07-25T15:25:00.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140964/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140964/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-07-22","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make it his policy to collate information on the (a) amount spent by local authorities on electoral registration, (b) number of staff employed by local authorities on electoral registration and (c) local authorities with the (i) highest and (ii) lowest levels of electoral registration.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140965","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-08-06","<p>The importance of good quality food for patients, visitor and staff is recognised both in terms of improving health and for their overall experience of services. Patients have the right to receive tasty, nutritious and free food as part of their National Health Service treatment.</p><p> </p><p>Data is not collected centrally on the number of local senior or executive champions to drive local work on nutrition, the number of commissioners that reviewed existing service provision or agreed improvement trajectories as set out in the guidance.</p><p> </p><p>In July 2018 the Healthcare Food Standards and Strategy Group started a review of the national standards for Healthcare Food for patients, staff and visitors. This work is building on the Hospital Food Panel report of 2014 and is focusing on marking out the way in which organisations need to comply with the five core standards and bringing in a wealth of tools, resources and examples of good practice to help them achieve the standards.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill","280420 ; 280421 ; 280422","2019-08-06T14:26:28.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140965/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140965/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-07-22","Nutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has plans to update the Commissioning Excellent Nutrition and Hydration 2015-2018 NHS England guidance.","false","Biography information for Eleanor Smith","Wolverhampton South West","Eleanor Smith","280423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140966","Cabinet Office","false","2019-07-25","<p>Prior to the introduction of Individual Electoral Registration (IER) in 2014, the potential benefits of using Driving and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) data as part of implementing IER were assessed. This investigation demonstrated that DVLA data could not readily be used to verify individuals’ identity, nor ascertain the names and addresses of people who are not registered but are entitled to be registered to vote.</p><p>The Government decided upon using National Insurance Numbers for verifying applicant’s identities during the registration process.</p><p>The Government is committed to increasing the levels of voter registration and voter registration processes are subject to ongoing review.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-07-25T15:24:49.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140966/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140966/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-07-22","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he has made a recent assessment of the potential merits of using vehicle registration databases held by the Driving and Vehicle Licensing Agency to increase levels of voter registration.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140967","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-08-05","<p>The Electoral Commission’s performance standards framework has not involved any formal notifications to Members of Parliament since 2014. Assessments of the performance of EROs are made annually by the Commission and the details of any ERO who has not met the standards in full are made available on the Commission’s website.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-08-05T10:27:29.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140967/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140967/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-07-22","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what steps have been taken by the Electoral Commission to inform hon. Members of the performance of electoral registration officers in their (a) constituency and (b) local authority.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140968","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-08-05","<p>The Electoral Commission’s performance standards framework has not involved any element of self-assessment by Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) since 2014.</p><p>The Commission has not assessed any ERO as not meeting this specific element of the performance standards since its inclusion in 2016.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-08-05T10:28:20.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140968/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140968/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-07-22","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, which electoral registration officers identified themselves as below standard at using information services to (a) verify entries in the register of electors and (b) identify potential new electors in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140969","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-07-31","<p>The Ministry of Justice will seek to find efficiency and affordability savings to fund the cost of the award.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-07-31T15:23:22.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140969/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140969/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-07-22","Prison Officers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the announcement, Pay rise for prison officers 2019, published by his Department on 22 July 2019, how much additional funding the Treasury has allocated to his Department for the pay award.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","280424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140970","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-08-05","<p>The Electoral Commission’s performance standards framework has not included any formal notifications to Members of Parliament since 2014. Assessments of the performance of Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) are made annually by the Commission and the details of any ERO who has not met the standards in full are made available on the Commission’s website.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-08-05T10:29:36.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140970/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140970/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-07-22","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, how many letters the Electoral Commission has written to hon. Members as a result of their electoral registration officers having failed at least one standard performance indicator in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140971","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-07-30","<p>The number of new officers appointed to work in public sector prisons and youth custody establishments between 1 April 2017 and the 31 March 2019 is published in the Quarterly Workforce Statistics for HM Prison and Probation Service at table 8a -<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/hm-prison-and-probation-service-workforce-quarterly-march-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/hm-prison-and-probation-service-workforce-quarterly-march-2019</a></p><p> </p><p>Additional funding of £106m was announced by the Secretary of State on 3 November 2016, for an additional 2,500 prison officer posts, which have now been filled. With growth, the £100m equates to £112m for the 2019/20 financial year, £97m of which is for public sector prisons.</p><p> </p><p>Our recruitment drive continues to replace turnover in officer numbers and meet required staffing levels across the prison estate. We constantly monitor the need for further funding.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-07-30T14:45:41.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140971/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140971/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-07-22","Prison Officers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many additional prison officers have been recruited since 31 March 2017; and how many of those posts were funded by the additional funding allocated by the Treasury at that time; and what additional funding the Treasury has allocated for the recruitment of prison offices since 31 March 2019.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","280425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140972","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-07-25","<p>The England Infected Blood Support Scheme (EIBSS) does not currently have direct support provisions for palliative care arrangements. EIBSS does however support beneficiaries to manage their health conditions via discretionary one-off payments.</p><p>Discretionary one-off payments are a form of financial support that beneficiaries and bereaved spouses/partners may apply for to cover the cost of certain essential, health-related items or services.</p><p>Some examples of the one-off payments we support are for home adaptations and repairs to support an individual’s medical conditions, assisting with respite breaks to aid recovery from periods of ill health and supporting the attendance of appointments by providing payments for car repairs and travel costs.</p><p>A full list of the items or services currently supported through EIBSS is available on the NHS Business Services Authority website at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/support-scheme-members/discretionary-support-scheme" target="_blank">https://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/support-scheme-members/discretionary-support-scheme</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2019-07-25T16:01:54.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140972/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140972/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-07-22","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment has been made of the adequacy of palliative care arrangements and support in place for the victims of the contaminated blood scandal.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","280426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140973","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-08-05","<p>The Electoral Commission’s performance standards framework has not involved any element of self-assessment by Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) since 2014.</p><p>Assessments of the performance of EROs are made annually by the Commission and the details of any ERO who has not met the standards in full are made available on the Commission’s website.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-08-05T10:21:57.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140973/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140973/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-07-22","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, with reference to the Answer of 5 July 2011 to Question 63427 on Electoral Register, which electoral registration officers rated themselves too highly in their self-assessment and had their ratings reduced in each year since 2014.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140974","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-24","<p>There are no staff who are paid below the living wage of £8.21 in the Department.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2019-07-24T09:04:18.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140974/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140974/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether all directly employed staff in his Department are paid at least the living wage.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","280196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140975","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-24","<p>MHCLG engage any agency or contractor staff through the Public Sector Resourcing framework and all agencies must be signed up to that framework. This service is provided through Alexander Mann Solutions. There is one exception to this where we have engaged Hays to support bringing in finance expertise on a short time basis.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2019-07-24T09:04:59.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140975/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140975/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140975/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, which agencies supply staff working in his Department.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","280197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140976","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-24","<p>The Government does not routinely hold or collect data to identify public buildings that are frequently visited by the public. Therefore, we have not made an assessment of the current levels of non-compliance in relation to display energy certificates.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-07-24T16:31:50.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140976/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140976/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-22","Public Buildings: Display Energy Certificates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the trends in the level of non-compliance with the Energy Performance of Buildings Directive regulations, for the requirement to have a valid Display Energy Certificate across all public buildings.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","280110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140977","Home Office","false","2019-07-31","<p>Sopra Steria Ltd (SSL) monitors the performance of the UKVCAS website and regularly reviews feedback from customers to ensure the website meets their needs and expectations.</p><p>So far, since service inception in November, the following improvements have been made to the online booking system:</p><p><br>- more detailed information in the FAQs section to help customers resolve problems <br>- improved visibility of appointments by expanding the number of locations that customers can view from four to eight. <br>- extended period for customers booking appointments from four to six weeks for core service points and from two to four weeks for enhanced service points.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy","280162","2019-07-31T15:27:16.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140977/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140977/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-22","Visas: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what representations he has received on the efficiency of the UK Visa and Citizenship Application Services online appointment booking system; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Dame Louise Ellman","280157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140978","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-08-05","<p>We know from our research of the electoral registers that voters from BME communities are less likely to be registered to vote when compared with white voters.</p><p>As part of all of its public awareness campaigns ahead of elections, the Electoral Commission provides voter registration resources to a wide range of groups or individuals, to use in encouraging registration. These are freely available via the Commission’s website or its ‘Roll Call’ newsletter, to which anyone can subscribe.</p><p>We also identify specific organisations who could help promote registration to under-registered groups and actively provide these partners with resources: these have recently included, for example, the Council of African and Caribbean Churches and the Muslim Women’s network. It also works closely with Electoral Registration Officers, who hold many important relationships with church and community leaders to promote voter registration at a local level.</p><p>The Commission most recently contacted Operation Black Vote ahead of the Government’s voter ID pilots which took place in May 2019, to seek a contribution to its statutory evaluation of the pilots. It did not receive a response.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-08-05T10:30:44.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140978/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140978/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-07-22","Electoral Register: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what recent discussions the Commission has had with (a) church and community leaders from black and minority ethnic communities and (b) Operation Black Vote on increasing registration levels for voters in those communities.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","280158"
