"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140993","Cabinet Office","false","2019-07-25","<p>The Civil Service do not gather information on individual medical conditions.</p><p>United Kingdom Security Vetting (UKSV), the UK’s centralised vetting provider, does not collate or report on specific medical conditions. This is due to vetting confidentiality. While medical conditions may be collected as part of vetting processes, these are recorded in narrative form. Reviewing the narrative data would require individual examination of many thousands of records. Similarly, it is not possible to collate data for withdrawals or suspensions citing medical factors, due to how this is recorded. Regardless, individuals are not denied clearance, or have clearances revoked, solely on the basis of possessing a particular medical condition. Rather, Vetting Officers, Medical Advisers and other staff build a holistic understanding of each candidate to assess any vulnerabilities or risk factors and make a judgement accordingly.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","280433","2019-07-25T15:24:41.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140993/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140993/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-07-22","Vetting: Hyperactivity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many individuals with ADHD have been given security clearance and then had that clearance withdrawn in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dr Rupa Huq","Ealing Central and Acton","Dr Rupa Huq","280432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140994","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-24","<p>The table below sets out the Department’s spend on software licences as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Spend (nearest £000s inc VAT)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>762</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>1,102</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018/19</p></td><td><p>2,422</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The increase in 2018/19 is mainly due to the modernisation of key elements of the MHCLG IT services which amounted to £1,322k as part of the roll-out of the IT Modernisation Programme.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2019-07-24T09:11:05.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140994/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140994/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Computer Software","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how much his Department spent on software licences in (a) 2016, (b) 2017 and (c) 2018.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","280203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140995","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-07-25","<p>A number of central planning and co-ordination teams have been established within the Department to lead and manage the work required to prepare for the UK’s exit from the EU. As of June 2019 there were a total of 69 people working in these teams. In addition other MHCLG staff who are working on related matters to the UK's withdrawal from the EU as part of their business as usual activities.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-07-25T07:14:26.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140995/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140995/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-07-22","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many officials in his office are working on matters relating to the UK's withdrawal from the the EU.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","280204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140996","Home Office","false","2019-07-24","<p>The Home Office does not collect this information. Data on electrical fires and those caused by smoking are available in tables 6.02 and 6.05 here:<br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables#cause-of-fire%20" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables#cause-of-fire </a>but we do not collect information on the tenure of the property in which the fire took place.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-07-24T15:28:14.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140996/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140996/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-22","Private Rented Housing: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the number and proportion of domestic fires in the private rented sector in England that have occurred as a result of (a) smoking and (b) electrical fires since 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","280205"
